aa(lp207
VWe don't know how important hand washing is for flu \u2014
p208
aVshocking. One assumes it's a good idea to wash your hands a lot.
p209
aVBut actually in scientific community there is great debate
p210
aVabout what percentage of flu transmission between people
p211
aVis from sneezing and coughing
p212
aVand what percentage is on your hands.
p213
aVThe Institute of Medicine tried to look at the masking question.
p214
aVCan we figure out a way, since we know we won't have enough masks
p215
aVbecause we don't make them in America anymore,
p216
aVthey're all made in China \u2014
p217
aVdo we need N95? A state-of-the-art, top-of-the-line,
p218
aVmust-be-fitted-to-your-face mask?
p219
aVOr can we get away with some different kinds of masks?
p220
aVIn the SARS epidemic, we learned in Hong Kong
p221
aVthat most of transmission was because
p222
aVpeople were removing their masks improperly.
p223
aVAnd their hand got contaminated with the outside of the mask,
p224
aVand then they rubbed their nose. Bingo! They got SARS.
p225
aVIt wasn't flying microbes.
p226
aVIf you go online right now, you'll get so much phony-baloney information.
p227
aVYou'll end up buying \u2014 this is called an N95 mask. Ridiculous.
p228
aVWe don't actually have a standard
p229
aVfor what should be the protective gear for the first responders,
p230
aVthe people who will actually be there on the front lines.
p231
aa(lp232
VAnd Tamiflu. You've probably heard of this drug,
p233
aVmade by Hoffmann-La Roche, patented drug.
p234
aVThere is some indication
p235
aVthat it may buy you some time in the midst of an outbreak.
p236
aVShould you take Tamiflu for a long period of time,
p237
aVwell, one of the side effects is suicidal ideations.
p238
aVA public health survey analyzed the effect
p239
aVthat large-scale Tamiflu use would have,
p240
aVactually shows it counteractive
p241
aVto public health measures, making matters worse.
p242
aVAnd here is the other interesting thing:
p243
aVwhen a human being ingests Tamiflu, only 20 percent
p244
aVis metabolized appropriately
p245
aVto be an active compound in the human being.
p246
aVThe rest turns into a stable compound,
p247
aVwhich survives filtration into the water systems,
p248
aVthereby exposing the very aquatic birds that would carry flu
p249
aVand providing them a chance
p250
aVto breed resistant strains.
p251
aVAnd we now have seen Tamiflu-resistant strains
p252
aVin both Vietnam in person-to-person transmission,
p253
aVand in Egypt in person-to-person transmission.
p254
aVSo I personally think that our life expectancy
p255
aVfor Tamiflu as an effective drug
p256
aVis very limited \u2014 very limited indeed.
p257
aa(lp258
VNevertheless most of the governments
p259
aVhave based their whole flu policies
p260
aVon building stockpiles of Tamiflu.
p261
aVRussia has actually stockpiled enough
p262
aVfor 95 percent of all Russians.
p263
aVWe've stockpiled enough for 30 percent.
p264
aVWhen I say enough, that's two weeks worth.
p265
aVAnd then you're on your own because
p266
aVthe pandemic is going to last for 18 to 24 months.
p267
aVSome of the poorer countries
p268
aVthat have had the most experience with H5N1 have built up stockpiles;
p269
aVthey're already expired. They are already out of date.
p270
aVWhat do we know from 1918,
p271
aVthe last great pandemic?
p272
aVThe federal government abdicated most responsibility.
p273
aVAnd so we ended up with this wild patchwork of regulations
p274
aVall over America.
p275
aVEvery city, county, state did their own thing.
p276
aVAnd the rules
p277
aVand the belief systems were wildly disparate.
p278
aVIn some cases all schools, all churches,
p279
aVall public venues were closed.
p280
aa(lp281
VThe pandemic circulated three times in 18 months
p282
aVin the absence of commercial air travel.
p283
aVThe second wave was the mutated, super-killer wave.
p284
aVAnd in the first wave we had enough healthcare workers.
p285
aVBut by the time the second wave hit
p286
aVit took such a toll among the healthcare workers
p287
aVthat we lost most of our doctors and nurses that were on the front lines.
p288
aVOverall we lost 700,000 people.
p289
aVThe virus was 100 percent lethal to pregnant women
p290
aVand we don't actually know why.
p291
aVMost of the death toll was 15 to 40 year-olds \u2014
p292
aVrobustly healthy young adults.
p293
aVIt was likened to the plague.
p294
aVWe don't actually know how many people died.
p295
aVThe low-ball estimate is 35 million.
p296
aVThis was based on European and North American data.
p297
aa(lp298
VA new study by Chris Murray at Harvard
p299
aVshows that if you look at the databases that were kept
p300
aVby the Brits in India,
p301
aVthere was a 31-fold greater death rate among the Indians.
p302
aVSo there is a strong belief that in places of poverty
p303
aVthe death toll was far higher.
p304
aVAnd that a more likely toll
p305
aVis somewhere in the neighborhood of 80 to 100 million people
p306
aVbefore we had commercial air travel.
p307
aVSo are we ready?
p308
aVAs a nation, no we're not.
p309
aVAnd I think even those in the leadership
p310
aVwould say that is the case,
p311
aVthat we still have a long ways to go.
p312
aa(lp313
VSo what does that mean for you? Well the first thing is,
p314
aVI wouldn't start building up personal stockpiles of anything \u2014
p315
aVfor yourself, your family, or your employees \u2014
p316
aVunless you've really done your homework.
p317
aVWhat mask works, what mask doesn't work.
p318
aVHow many masks do you need?
p319
aVThe Institute of Medicine study felt that
p320
aVyou could not recycle masks.
p321
aVWell if you think it's going to last 18 months,
p322
aVare you going to buy 18 months worth of masks
p323
aVfor every single person in your family?
p324
aa(lp325
VWe don't know \u2014 again with Tamiflu,
p326
aVthe number one side effect of Tamiflu is
p327
aVflu-like symptoms.
p328
aVSo then how can you tell
p329
aVwho in your family has the flu
p330
aVif everybody is taking Tamiflu?
p331
aVIf you expand that out to think of a whole community,
p332
aVor all your employees in your company,
p333
aVyou begin to realize how limited
p334
aVthe Tamiflu option might be.
p335
aVEverybody has come up to me and said,
p336
aVwell I'll stockpile water or, I'll stockpile food, or what have you.
